Word popup gloss fix, mobile back button mirror, poetry layout across all texts

- Word popup: show the head English word next to the transliteration for words
  with a long (3+ word) gloss; fall back to the full phrase if no head word so the
  English line is never blank (was inconsistent — long glosses showed nothing)
- Mobile overview/intro sheets: the back "‹" now sits in the exact spot the word
  tab's ✕ uses (same 32×32 box, same right edge / top padding)
- Poetry books (Psalms, Proverbs, Job, Song of Solomon, Lamentations, Ecclesiastes)
  now stay verse-per-line in KJV/BSB/ESV/NIV too, matching ABP (was ABP-only)

